id: pm-8778
title: "Architecture boundary ratchet: prevent new CLI/MCP private core imports while SDK promotion shrinks the baseline"
description: "Enforce the SDK-first migration mechanically with a static quality ratchet: src/cli and src/mcp may not add new private src/core import edges, may not use computed dynamic imports that bypass the inventory, and must remove stale baseline entries as primitives move into src/sdk. Duplicate check: no existing boundary-gate item; static-quality-gate existed but had no import-boundary ratchet."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: architecture,"area:ci","area:sdk",quality-gate
created_at: "2026-07-05T04:54:30.762Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-05T09:58:54.232Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "Static quality gate fails CI on new src/core import edges from src/cli/src/mcp, computed dynamic imports from boundary sources, or stale baseline entries; allowlist starts at current state and ratchets down per promotion task, reaching zero when all primitives are promoted; rule documented in architecture docs and SDK inventory"
parent: pm-usfg
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Extended scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs with an SDK import-boundary ratchet backed by scripts/release/sdk-import-boundary-baseline.json and regression coverage. The gate fails on new private src/core imports from src/cli or src/mcp, unsupported computed dynamic imports, and stale baseline entries."
expected_result: CI/static quality blocks any growth in private core imports from presentation layers while SDK primitives are promoted incrementally.
actual_result: "Current baseline is clean at 857 unique private core import edges; focused tests, linked pm tests, lint, security scan, temp dogfood, Sentry/telemetry gate, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 all passed."
comments[19]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-05T05:16:13.080Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation start: boundary gate will start as a current-state allowlist/ratchet rather than pretending the CLI is already SDK-only. This keeps CI enforceable immediately and lets each primitive-promotion item shrink the baseline."
  "2026-07-05T05:51:00.392Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: implemented SDK import-boundary ratchet in scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs with current-state baseline scripts/release/sdk-import-boundary-baseline.json. The gate scans src/cli.ts, src/cli/**, and src/mcp/** and fails on new private src/core imports or stale baseline entries. Current baseline is clean: 101 boundary source files scanned, 857 unique private src/core edges, 857 baseline edges, no new_private_core_imports and no stale_baseline_imports. Verification passed: focused static-quality-gate spec 62 tests; pm linked test run 2/2; pnpm lint (ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, static quality); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage 263 files / 5411 tests at 100/100/100/100; pnpm security:scan clean; docs/skills gate clean; git diff --check clean."
  "2026-07-05T05:51:11.973Z",claude-code-agent,"Manual dogfood evidence: after npm install -g . from this checkout, a fresh temp project at /tmp/tmp.BGd7iO6089 passed pm init --defaults, pm create Task with acceptance criteria, pm list-open, pm install kanban --project, pm profile list/show, pm profile apply kanban --dry-run, and pm health --check-only --summary --json with health_ok=true."
  "2026-07-05T06:04:08.995Z",claude-code-agent,"Pre-push Greptile review 92d93b38-8ef1-46a9-9b8f-4e9b2f36eefc follow-up: addressed both findings before push. The scanner now recursively detects string-literal dynamic import() calls into src/core instead of only top-level import/export declarations, and baseline-read failures now return empty violation arrays with error populated so JSON consumers do not confuse scan failure with new import violations. Focused static-quality-gate spec and full coverage reran successfully after the fix."
  "2026-07-05T06:24:42.165Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #431 follow-up: GitHub Windows regression (Node 24) failed because the SDK-boundary unit test forced node:path to POSIX while using a Windows drive-letter temp root, causing collectPrivateCoreImportEdges to resolve no candidates. Fixed the test to exercise the native path implementation for the SDK import-boundary scenario. Verification after fix: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/static-quality-gate.spec.ts (62 passed); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (263 files, 5411 tests, 100/100/100/100); pnpm lint; pnpm security:scan; git diff --check; pnpm changelog:pm:check."
  "2026-07-05T06:46:22.660Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Evidence: addressed PR review findings by making the SDK import-boundary ratchet fail closed for computed dynamic imports while still accepting string and no-substitution-template specifiers. Validation passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/static-quality-gate.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (263 files, 5412 tests, 100/100/100/100); pnpm lint; pnpm security:scan; pnpm changelog:pm:check; pnpm quality:docs-skills; git diff --check; pm health --check-only --summary --json; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json (history drift ok, pre-existing resolution metadata warnings remain); node scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs --json --telemetry-mode required --sentry-window-days 14 --max-critical 0 --max-high 0 (Sentry 0 critical/high in 14d, telemetry ok at 1.05% finish error rate)."
  "2026-07-05T07:02:37.446Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Greptile follow-up: local review beace340-5084-4dc5-b208-209690506bce reported two P2 findings. Fixed both by validating baseline source paths against SDK boundary scope for clearer malformed-baseline failures and by reusing the prefiltered boundary file list inside checkSdkImportBoundary. Verification after fixes passed: focused static-quality-gate spec (63 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (263 files, 5412 tests, 100/100/100/100); pnpm lint; pnpm security:scan; pnpm changelog:pm:check; pnpm quality:docs-skills; git diff --check; pm health --check-only --summary --json; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json (history drift ok; existing resolution warnings unchanged)."
  "2026-07-05T07:19:47.378Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Review fix evidence: addressed current PR #431 bot feedback by limiting stale SDK-boundary baseline comparisons to scanned boundary sources, accepting import attributes as supported dynamic imports, and normalizing repo-relative paths to POSIX separators after path.relative for Windows safety. Validation after the fix: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/static-quality-gate.spec.ts passed 63 tests; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 263 files / 5412 tests with 100/100/100/100 coverage; pnpm lint passed including ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, and static quality; pnpm security:scan passed with no tracked credential-like secrets; pnpm quality:docs-skills passed; git diff --check passed; pnpm changelog:pm:check unchanged using pm-changelog 2026.6.30; pm health --check-only --summary --json ok; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json ok with known validate_resolution_missing_fields:268 warning and history_drift ok; sentry-telemetry-gate ok with Sentry 0 critical/high and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct 1.05."
  "2026-07-05T07:30:09.008Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Greptile follow-up evidence: local pre-push Greptile review flagged that text-mode SDK import-boundary failures hid unsupported_dynamic_import counts when baseline loading also failed. Fixed printQualityFailureSummary to always emit the unsupported dynamic import count in the SDK boundary error path and added a regression covering missing baseline plus computed dynamic import. Validation after this fix: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/static-quality-gate.spec.ts passed 64 tests; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 263 files / 5413 tests with 100/100/100/100 coverage; pnpm lint passed including ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, and static quality; pnpm security:scan clean; pnpm quality:docs-skills passed; git diff --check passed; pnpm changelog:pm:check unchanged with pm-changelog 2026.6.30."
  "2026-07-05T08:02:27.934Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Post-review evidence: added src/mcp.ts to the SDK import-boundary source set and extended the ratchet so missing/deleted boundary sources are reported as stale baseline entries without reintroducing subset-scan false positives. Re-verified with focused static-quality gate spec, full coverage (263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines), lint, security scan, docs/skills gate, changelog:pm:check, git diff --check, pm health, pm validate, and sentry telemetry gate."
  "2026-07-05T08:12:07.532Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Final pre-push evidence: closed Greptile's remaining parser-hardening notes by requiring SDK import-boundary baseline version=1 and rejecting baseline imports outside src/core/. Focused static-quality gate spec passed (65 tests). Full coverage passed again (263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines). Rerun gates passed: pnpm lint, pnpm security:scan, pnpm quality:docs-skills, git diff --check, pnpm changelog:pm:check unchanged with pm-changelog 2026.6.30, pm health clean, pm validate history_drift ok with known validate_resolution_missing_fields:268 warning, and sentry-telemetry-gate ok (Sentry 0 critical/high, telemetry finish_error_rate_pct 1.04)."
  "2026-07-05T08:20:54.521Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Greptile P2 resolution: removed the redundant literal-backslash replacement from relativeToRepo so POSIX filenames containing a literal backslash cannot be misnormalized while platform separator normalization remains intact. Validation after the fix: focused static-quality spec passed 65 tests; full coverage passed 263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm lint passed with ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, and static quality; security scan clean; docs/skills gate clean; git diff --check clean; changelog:pm:check unchanged with pm-changelog 2026.6.30; pm health clean; pm validate history_drift ok with known validate_resolution_missing_fields:268; sentry-telemetry-gate ok with Sentry 0 critical/high and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct 1.04."
  "2026-07-05T08:32:04.345Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Final Greptile follow-up evidence: simplified the unsupported dynamic-import arity guard for readability and documented that the SDK-boundary ratchet intentionally counts type-only core imports and re-exports as private core contract coupling. Validation after the fix: focused static-quality spec 65 tests; full coverage 263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm lint; pnpm security:scan; pnpm quality:docs-skills; git diff --check; pnpm changelog:pm:check unchanged with pm-changelog 2026.6.30; pm health clean; pm validate history_drift ok with known validate_resolution_missing_fields:268; sentry-telemetry-gate ok with no critical/high Sentry issues and telemetry finish error rate 1.04%."
  "2026-07-05T08:39:45.695Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Greptile style follow-up evidence: converted the two new SDK-boundary AST walkers to const visit arrow functions to match the existing static-quality-gate walker convention. Validation after this final style fix: focused static-quality gate spec passed 65 tests; full coverage passed 263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm lint passed with ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, and static quality."
  "2026-07-05T08:59:26.129Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Gemini follow-up evidence: hardened SDK boundary scanning for deleted boundary input paths and direct repo-root src/core import specifiers. Missing boundary paths are skipped during AST reads so deleted files do not crash the gate, while stale baseline comparison still reports removed baseline edges. Direct src/... specifiers now resolve from repoRoot, so src/core aliases cannot bypass the ratchet. Validation: focused static-quality gate spec 65 tests; full coverage 263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm lint; security scan; docs/skills; git diff --check; changelog:pm:check unchanged; pm health; pm validate; sentry-telemetry-gate."
  "2026-07-05T09:06:19.380Z",codex-sdk-agent,"CodeRabbit follow-up evidence: aligned SDK boundary docs and parent epic metadata with the current ratchet scope. docs/SDK_PRIMITIVE_INVENTORY.md now includes src/mcp.ts in the boundary scope and derives scan/edge counts from the baseline plus quality-static output instead of hardcoding drift-prone snapshot numbers. pm-usfg acceptance criteria now names src/cli.ts, src/cli/**, src/mcp.ts, and src/mcp/** and describes the enforceable CI ratchet baseline while preserving the SDK-only end state."
  "2026-07-05T09:20:44.058Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Final bot-review follow-up evidence: addressed Greptile import-equals ratchet finding by detecting TypeScript import-equals external module references in boundary files, so import store = require('../core/...') is counted as a private core edge. Addressed Gemini test hygiene finding by clearing process.exitCode in the two SDK-boundary text-mode regression tests after asserting the failure. The duplicate parsing comment is acknowledged as a future optimization, not a correctness blocker. Validation: focused static-quality gate spec 65 tests; full coverage 263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm lint; pnpm security:scan; pnpm quality:docs-skills; git diff --check; changelog:pm:check unchanged; pm health; pm validate; sentry-telemetry-gate."
  "2026-07-05T09:38:22.010Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Greptile follow-up evidence: literal require() calls in SDK boundary files are now counted as import edges when the require specifier is a string literal, so const store = require('../core/...') cannot bypass the private core ratchet. Validation after the fix: focused static-quality gate spec passed 65 tests; full coverage passed 263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm lint passed with ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, and static quality; pnpm security:scan clean; pnpm quality:docs-skills passed; git diff --check clean; pnpm changelog:pm:check unchanged with pm-changelog 2026.6.30; pm health clean; pm validate history_drift ok with known validate_resolution_missing_fields:268; sentry-telemetry-gate ok with Sentry 0 critical/high and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct 1.04."
  "2026-07-05T09:58:54.232Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Greptile computed-require follow-up evidence: SDK boundary files now fail closed on non-literal require() calls, including require('../core/' + name) and require(target), by reporting computed_require in the unsupported module-reference list. Literal require('...') calls remain resolvable and are counted as private core edges. Validation after the fix: focused static-quality gate spec passed 65 tests; full coverage passed 263 files / 5414 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm lint passed with ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, and static quality; pnpm security:scan clean; pnpm quality:docs-skills passed; git diff --check clean; pnpm changelog:pm:check unchanged with pm-changelog 2026.6.30; pm health clean; pm validate history_drift ok with known validate_resolution_missing_fields:268; sentry-telemetry-gate ok with Sentry 0 critical/high and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct 1.05."
